<BaseLayout title="About Cmprly" description="Independent SaaS comparisons for smart buyers.">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem 1rem;">
    <h1 style="font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">About Cmprly</h1>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <strong>Cmprly is an independent comparison platform for software and SaaS tools.</strong> We help solopreneurs, creators, and small businesses make smarter buying decisions — without the marketing fluff.
    </p>
    <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0 0.75rem;">How We Work</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:1rem;">
      Every comparison on Cmprly is built from publicly verifiable data: official pricing pages, feature documentation, public benchmarks, and changelogs. We do not accept sponsored rankings. We do not run "pay to be on top" placements. When we recommend a tool, it's because the data supports it.
    </p>
    <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0 0.75rem;">Our Methodology</h2>
    <ul style="margin-left:1.5rem;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.75;">
      <li><strong>Data collection:</strong> We pull pricing, features, and limitations from official vendor pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Structured comparison:</strong> Every tool is scored against the same criteria — pricing, feature depth, ease of use, and real-user feedback.</li>
      <li><strong>Quarterly review:</strong> Every article is rechecked at least once per quarter. The "Last verified" date tells you when.</li>
      <li><strong>No fake reviews:</strong> We don't fabricate "hands-on testing" when we haven't done it. When our analysis is based on public data, we say so.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;margin:2rem 0 0.75rem;">Contact</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.75;">
      Questions, corrections, or partnership inquiries? Reach us at <strong>hello@cmprly.com</strong>.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#999;margin-top:2rem;">Last updated: July 2026</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
